<br>
Revised Premise: The year remains the same as does much of the basic background: US, China, and &quot;new kid&quot; Brazil are the big military powers, with each having a near death-grip on their populations but not much else.  A revised UN serves as a balance against the superpowers, with the transfer of power from the dissolved security council to the general assembly, an independant - but severely constrained - military force, and a network of reconnaisance satellites monitoring global hotspots and regions under world sanction.  <br>
<br>
Space exploration remains much the same as in the original premise with a few modifications: Near-Earth space is divided among national and corporate interests, with the Japan-dominated space tourism industry and coalitions of European-Japanese-Chinese lunar mining bases.  At L5 is the Avalon colony, which was built by a utopian conglomerate, and is now the largest advocate for a colonization proposal opposed by the old superpowers and other repressive regimes.  Outside of near-Earth space, the United Nations Space Exploration Agency is the primary force of human expansion, maintaining refuelling stations in strategic orbits matching Earth's, and building research colonies on Mars and the Jovian moon Callisto.  Weapons - beyond basic station and colony security - are forbidden outside of Earth's atmosphere by treaty.<br>
<br>
The fragile &quot;pax humana&quot; that exists in 2047 is threatened when an alien ship crashes on Callisto.  The vessel, and its crew, become first pawns - then players - in the sociopolitical<br>
<br>
Primary Characters (both good and bad guys): <br>
Alexandria Markham - scientist at Nar Base on Callisto<br>
Micheal Langstrom - robotics engineer, Nar Base<br>
(name TBD) - Chinese Space Force captain, currently spacecraft pilot at Nar Base<br>
(name TBD) - American General (three stars), US Space Force<br>
(name TBD) - American Vice President and member of the &quot;Cabal&quot;<br>
(name TBD) - UN Secretary General<br>
(name TBD) - Avalonian council member<br>
(name TBD) - Avalonian citizen<br>
(name TBD) - Alaskan governor<br>
(name TBD) - alien &quot;commander&quot;<br>
