<br>
Plot Structure as it stands now (very sketchy)<br>
<br>
Act 1:<br>
We are introduced to much of the primary characters - some only sketchily, and to the problems facing those characters; the overriding issue being the colony proposal put before the General Assembly.  Some characters see it as good, some as bad, and act according to their own agendas.<br>
<br>
The alien ship crashes, and Nar Base begins to conduct research, unwittingly awaking the aliens and contact is made.  The news of contact ripples through the human sphere of influence, hastening a shady alliance between ambitious persons within the old superpowers.  Rumours circle within military circles of a new superweapon, known only as &quot;Archangel&quot;<br>
<br>
At Nar base, on Callisto, the pilot is suddenly recalled by his government - he is unable to say why, but he is convinced it cannot be good.  <br>
<br>
On Earth, the General learns the true nature of Archangel - a massive network of high-powered laser satellites - and after some digging, learns their horrible purpose.  He is too late, however, to stop the plans of the Cabal, who arrange for a little &quot;regime change&quot; of their own, by some careful assasinations and using Archangel to gut the UN by destroying key buildings.  So ends Act 1.<br>
<br>
Act 2<br>
The Cabal spreads its influence out by sending forces to sieze the refuelling stations, as well as the settlements on Luna, Mars, and Callisto.  Archangel, after its flashy debut, is down for the count while certain satellite systems have to be replaced.  In response to the initial invasions, Avalon colony unveils a small military force they had been building in secret, and uses it to counter the superpowers.  Alex, Mike, and the rest of Nar base are increasingly worried by the news from Earth, but, being unable to do anything about it, concentrate more on the aliens, who are themselves torn between their fear of the humans and their increasingly desperate need for help.  <br>
<br>
The Avalon-Cabal war heats up and splits down the middle as American and Chinese members of the Cabal turn against each other - but still the fighting remains confined to space, for now.  Other nations become concerned enough to tighten up defenses on their own borders, and small flare wars break out.  Remnants of the UN try to reorganize and at the same time try to end the smaller wars.  The General is now a fugitive, and unlikely guardian for the Secretary-General, who was among the few people to escape the destruction of the General Assembly in Act 1.  <br>
<br>
At Nar Base, halting steps towards cooperation between human and alien are dealt a massive blow as a Cabal mole is uncovered just after sabotaging part of the main drive for the alien ship.  Through this incident, the aliens get their first good look at the chaos brewing insystem.<br>
<br>
The fighting spreads to Mars, where the pilot finds himself among the Chinese force sent to &quot;secure&quot; the colony.  <br>
<br>
Act 2 ends with the invasion of Nar base by Cabal forces.  The aliens flee, with Mike as passenger/prisoner.  Alex and the others are captured and sent back to Earth for interrogation.<br>
<br>
Act 3 - the resolution - remains unplotted.<br>
<br>
Critiques are requested.<br>
